feed.title: News Feed
feed.subtitle: Here are some articles I found interesting

entry.title: (FROM ATOM FEED)Team World beats Team Europe to claim back-to-back Laver Cup titles
entry.summary: Team World won eight of the nine matches played over three days to cruise to a second win.

entry.title: (FROM ATOM FEED)Keonigsegg Gemera Boosts Output to 2300 HP with new optional V8
entry.summary: The production version of Koenigsegg's four-seat supercar will offer a 5.0-liter V-8 along with the original three-cylinder powertrain, with both engines mated to a single e-motor.

entry.title: (FROM ATOM FEED)Mars Perseverance rover engineer credits Queens high school
entry.summary: Vishnu Sridhar is the lead systems engineer for Perseverance's SuperCam. He grew up in Rego Park, Queens, and attended Aviation High School in Sunnyside.

entry.title: (FROM ATOM FEED)Coast Guard arrests a man trying to run a giant hamster wheel across the Atlantic
entry.summary: Reza Baluchi was taken in by the U.S. Coast Guard last week while trying to cross the Atlantic in a "hydro pod" made of buoys. Authorities in Flagler County, Fla., responded to Baluchi and his vessel in 2021 and posted photos of his vessel on Facebook.

entry.title: (FROM ATOM FEED)Sierra Space raises $290 million
entry.summary: Sierra Space says a new $290 million funding round will support work on its Dream Chaser vehicles and commercial space station plans. Credit: Sierra Space
